  </div>

  <img src="/projects/minilink.gif" alt="MiniLink demo" class="rounded-lg w-full mb-8 border" />

  <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Problem</div>
  <div class="mb-8 text-base text-justify">
    Every public URL shortener sends your links (and your users' clicks) through someone else's servers.
    More importantly for portfolio purposes: public shorteners don't require writing a Dockerfile,
    wiring up Docker Compose, or deploying to a cloud platform. MiniLink exists to demonstrate those
    DevOps fundamentals in a scope small enough to reason about completely.
  </div>

  <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Solution</div>
  <div class="mb-8 text-base text-justify">
    A self-hosted URL shortener where <code>POST /shorten</code> returns a short code and
    <code>GET /&#123;code&#125;</code> issues a 302 redirect. Every redirect increments a hit counter
    in Postgres. A live HTMX dashboard shows the top 20 links by hits. Short-code lookups are served
    from Redis on the hot path â€” Postgres is only touched on a cache miss or a write.
  </div>

  <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Tech stack</div>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
    <table class="table table-zebra">
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><b>API</b></td><td>FastAPI Â· SQLModel</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Database</b></td><td>PostgreSQL (Railway managed)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Cache</b></td><td>Redis â€” read-through cache, 24-hour TTL (Railway managed)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Container</b></td><td>Docker â€” multi-stage build (builder â†’ runtime, â‰ˆ150 MB image)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Local dev</b></td><td>Docker Compose â€” one command brings up API + Postgres + Redis</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>CI/CD</b></td><td>GitHub Actions: lint (ruff) â†’ test (pytest) â†’ build image â†’ push to GHCR â†’ Railway auto-deploy</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Dashboard UI</b></td><td>HTMX + Tailwind CSS (no React, no build step)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><b>Deploy</b></td><td>Railway â€” managed services, GitHub App auto-deploy on push to main</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Architecture</div>
  <pre class="bg-base-300 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-3 text-sm">Browser
  â”‚
  â–¼
FastAPI  (Railway â€” Dockerfile, port 8080)
  â”‚
  â”œâ”€ short-code lookup
  â”‚       â”‚
